  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       THE KINDLED — an elemental being. A bare, weaponless humanoid the land
       wakes where raw magic pools. ElementalBeings wreathes it in its element
       (fire / water / stone / storm), drives its weakness, and forces it to
       charge; it carries no steel and throws no stones. Seeded into wild bands
       (ElementalWildsBehavior) and summoned through ElementalFactory. Body key
       is fixed (min==max) so every Kindled shares one bare, uniform shape
       rather than looking like an individual person.

       The body key must be a FULL, VALID body-properties key (~128 hex chars) —
       the one below is the base game's adult "BodyProperty.looter" min key. A
       short/truncated key (e.g. "0000000000000000") fails to parse and the body
       falls back to BodyProperties.Default, whose age is 0 — so every Kindled
       spawned as a NEWBORN/baby-scaled model. Keep the min==max age solidly
       adult too.

       CULTURE MUST BE "Culture.looters" (plural). The base game's bandit culture
       id is "looters"; "Culture.looter" (singular) does NOT resolve, and an
       unresolved culture is a placeholder with a null Name. When the player
       catches a heroless wild band, the engine opens the ordinary caught-party
       conversation (silenced to "..." by ElementalDialogue) and its very first
       line does string.Concat(... character.Culture ...), which calls
       CultureObject.ToString() → Name.ToString() → NRE, hard-crashing the game
       (ConversationManager.StartNew). This is why the Kindled crashed when it
       became its own troop but worked while the band was made of real looters
       (the real "looter" troop is culture "looters", valid). The same typo is in
       the Fire Worshipper troops below — any heroless band of them crashes the
       same way. It only bites HEROLESS parties: a hero leader is the conversation
       partner instead, so its (valid) culture is used.

       Equipment stays a single drab, weaponless garment: a conversable troop
       should carry a body, and the battle factory already guards a null
       FirstBattleEquipment with `FirstBattleEquipment ?? Equipment`.
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

  <NPCCharacter id="elemental_being"
                name="{=elemental_being_name}Elemental"
                age="30"
                level="30"
                culture="Culture.looters"
                default_group="Infantry"
                occupation="Bandit"
                is_basic_troop="false"
                is_hidden_in_encyclopedia="true">
    <face>
      <BodyPropertiesMin version="4" age="30.0" weight="0.5" build="0.7" key="0000000000000000111111111111111000001100000100000001000000100000000106030000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000001C040002"/>
      <BodyPropertiesMax version="4" age="30.0" weight="0.5" build="0.7" key="0000000000000000111111111111111000001100000100000001000000100000000106030000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000001C040002"/>
    </face>
    <Equipments>
      <!-- Weaponless by design; a plain garment only, so the body renders. -->
      <EquipmentRoster>
        <equipment slot="Body" id="Item.rough_tied_armor"/>
        <equipment slot="Leg"  id="Item.strapped_leather_boots"/>
      </EquipmentRoster>
    </Equipments>
    <skills>
      <skill id="Athletics"  value="150"/>
      <skill id="OneHanded"  value="80"/>
    </skills>
  </NPCCharacter>

